<span key="5a1e826c5dfa4528a9fa6cd8166db4d7"><span offset-key="5a1e826c5dfa4528a9fa6cd8166db4d7:0">Objectives in Labs</span></span>

## 

<span key="3796ae5a29fb41c58931626f1bec7c72"><span offset-key="3796ae5a29fb41c58931626f1bec7c72:0">What are Objectives?</span></span>

<span key="9577dae7e1b24fb2961549e6ef99354c"><span offset-key="9577dae7e1b24fb2961549e6ef99354c:0">Instead of Sprint Challenges, Labs uses </span>**Objectives**<span offset-key="9577dae7e1b24fb2961549e6ef99354c:2"> to assess your understanding and your contributions to your project.</span></span>

<span key="d0717a3ac83e49c0809f08cc9bc58d62"><span offset-key="d0717a3ac83e49c0809f08cc9bc58d62:0">Objectives are your ticket to graduationâ€”achieve them all, and you'll be ready to graduate! (Note that it will take a minimum of four sprints to achieve all your objectives, and you'll have up to eight sprints to do it.)</span></span>

<span key="375ba6600c734c7eb7a58b6a25956f19"><span offset-key="375ba6600c734c7eb7a58b6a25956f19:0">Your objectives are tailored to your roleâ€”another way to arm you with an experience more relevant to you.</span></span>

## 

<span key="b2525913be504a98a700f352999237b5"><span offset-key="b2525913be504a98a700f352999237b5:0">Objective Types</span></span>

# 

<span key="728c1217d16e44aa9c53c0a0aa606ebd"><span offset-key="728c1217d16e44aa9c53c0a0aa606ebd:0">UX Principles</span></span>

## 

<span key="16d5e3a15e1b41d7b2876d01465faa86"><span offset-key="16d5e3a15e1b41d7b2876d01465faa86:0">What is UX?</span></span>

<span key="42074d078b584592aa4f7d7ecc3045a4"><span offset-key="42074d078b584592aa4f7d7ecc3045a4:0">If the title of this module didn't already give it away, UX stands for </span>**user experience**<span offset-key="42074d078b584592aa4f7d7ecc3045a4:2">. UX is, ultimately, </span>**what users experience**<span offset-key="42074d078b584592aa4f7d7ecc3045a4:4"> when using a product.</span></span>

<span key="6c532bb60b6e4050acb8bc9d1fd3fe04"><span offset-key="6c532bb60b6e4050acb8bc9d1fd3fe04:0">We can hear you from here: "Well, that's vague." An apt observation! "UX" is a </span>*super*<span offset-key="6c532bb60b6e4050acb8bc9d1fd3fe04:2"> general term, and it's also constantly evolving. That's largely because user experience is a relatively new area of study, and we're learning more and more as products and the technologies used to build them evolve at an exponential pace.</span></span>

## 

<span key="a44939aa22584032bd81e725216747c9"><span offset-key="a44939aa22584032bd81e725216747c9:0">UX vs. UI</span></span>

<span key="a6f12d6882664c0b8bf5edc6878a8962"><span offset-key="a6f12d6882664c0b8bf5edc6878a8962:0">You've likely seen these terms bandied about, used interchangeably, or even in combination with each other: UI, UX, UI/UX, design, interaction design, UI design, UX design...</span></span>

<span key="3b87774eb770492da4a1358157606fce"><span offset-key="3b87774eb770492da4a1358157606fce:0">UI stands for </span>**user interface**<span offset-key="3b87774eb770492da4a1358157606fce:2"> (though </span>*sometimes*<span offset-key="3b87774eb770492da4a1358157606fce:4"> it can stand for "user interaction"â€”this isn't helping, is it...)</span></span>

<span key="96e4a417025147f4b505d8faff951303"><span offset-key="96e4a417025147f4b505d8faff951303:0">Ultimately, the distinction between these terms does matter, but </span>**it doesn't matter too much**<span offset-key="96e4a417025147f4b505d8faff951303:2">. What matters is that you understand that they represent various areas of focus that are ultimately trying to get at the same thing from different anglesâ€”</span>**how is a thing used**<span offset-key="96e4a417025147f4b505d8faff951303:4">?</span></span>

<span key="d61f419093824345be5aa0e2eb600091">**User experience (UX) design**<span offset-key="d61f419093824345be5aa0e2eb600091:1"> focuses on what happens to the user when they use the thing.</span></span>

<span key="bbb77b07421c47598101032bfe5ee199">**User interface (UI) design**<span offset-key="bbb77b07421c47598101032bfe5ee199:1"> focuses on the pieces of the thing the user interacts withâ€”hopefully informed by an anticipation and understanding of what their experience will or should be.</span></span>

## 

<span key="98c47be95ca04ae782c981c68622f308"><span offset-key="98c47be95ca04ae782c981c68622f308:0">UX Principles</span></span>

<span key="bdf13b031b504a5481f9c3ec8b8a4e47"><span offset-key="bdf13b031b504a5481f9c3ec8b8a4e47:0">in 2004, </span></span><a href="http://semanticstudios.com/user_experience_design/" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="dcd6da9054df46158741611a8270494a" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-8486_259-8487-237__"><span data-key="2e401219c965406b91f7bfcf08b81ccd"><span data-offset-key="2e401219c965406b91f7bfcf08b81ccd:0">Peter Morville (Links to an external site.)</span></span></span></a><span key="dafe4039bde046ed91fcc6609c3a876a"><span offset-key="dafe4039bde046ed91fcc6609c3a876a:0"> defined a core set of seven UX principles determining whether users will get value out of an experience:</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="9d68e7a6fc524721940e03ab2108c439"><span offset-key="9d68e7a6fc524721940e03ab2108c439:0">useful</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="4a449c7128304536872187fac41bd4ef"><span offset-key="4a449c7128304536872187fac41bd4ef:0">usable</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="912f08cf7c364316a6a04d91bdcf5be2"><span offset-key="912f08cf7c364316a6a04d91bdcf5be2:0">desirable</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="c0ad2dae29ea4727b09a997ed80095a2"><span offset-key="c0ad2dae29ea4727b09a997ed80095a2:0">valuable</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="f2099b0d62994c99bce2163411b595e0"><span offset-key="f2099b0d62994c99bce2163411b595e0:0">findable</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="c9990bf4ff3f4a15b4e72a8b9243fafa"><span offset-key="c9990bf4ff3f4a15b4e72a8b9243fafa:0">accessible</span></span>

-   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

    <span key="202b0cf4ef754e18ab3c44ea0a216ec9"><span offset-key="202b0cf4ef754e18ab3c44ea0a216ec9:0">credible</span></span>

<span key="91729896619a48db8623575ecb8a3b67"><span offset-key="91729896619a48db8623575ecb8a3b67:0">Like our seven principles of design, these seven principles of UX certainly aren't the only way to break up and talk about UX. But they do give us a helpful anchor for discussion!</span></span>
